AiPay / Agentic Shopping Assistant

Founder PRD v0.9

Working title

AiPay Home

Tagline

Shopping disappears. Control stays with you.

1. Executive summary

AiPay Home is a consumer convenience OS for shopping. It does not own inventory, act as a retailer, or try to replace merchants. Instead, it sits above existing retailers and marketplaces and becomes the user’s trusted layer for:
	•	product discovery
	•	delegated decision-making
	•	policy-based purchasing
	•	proactive replenishment
	•	post-purchase intervention and recovery

The product is built on a progressive trust ladder:
	•	Explore: the agent helps research and compare
	•	Delegate: the user gives a goal; the agent executes within policy
	•	Auto: the agent buys proactively in narrow, trusted categories

This is well timed. The market is now reorganizing around agentic commerce infrastructure: Google launched the open-source Universal Commerce Protocol in January 2026, explicitly to let AI interactions turn into direct buying across businesses and payment providers; Visa, Mastercard, and PayPal are all positioning their networks and tooling for agent-driven payments and checkout.  

