9. Product modes

9.1 Explore

User is uncertain.

Examples:
	•	“Find the best air fryer”
	•	“Need a new office chair”
	•	“Best healthy snacks for my kids”

Agent behavior:
	•	compares options
	•	groups choices by needs/archetypes
	•	explains tradeoffs
	•	learns from reactions
	•	does not buy without permission

Success criteria:
	•	reduced search time
	•	strong shortlist quality
	•	user feels understood

9.2 Delegate

User gives an outcome, not a detailed spec.

Examples:
	•	“Buy me a new phone”
	•	“Restock this week’s household basics”
	•	“Get more of the detergent we usually buy”

Agent behavior:
	•	infers preferences from history
	•	asks only missing questions
	•	prepares plan/cart/order
	•	executes inside policy
	•	escalates only when outside bounds

Success criteria:
	•	minimal clarification
	•	high recommendation acceptance
	•	low correction rate

9.3 Auto

The agent buys proactively in narrow, earned domains.

Examples:
	•	pantry staples
	•	paper goods
	•	pet food
	•	vitamins
	•	recurring pharmacy items
	•	replacement basics with known brand/size preferences

Agent behavior:
	•	monitors likely need
	•	chooses retailer/fulfillment according to policy
	•	buys automatically if confidence threshold is met
	•	notifies user
	•	allows stop/cancel/return where possible

Success criteria:
	•	high accept/no-change rate
	•	low regret
	•	low returns
	•	trust expansion

