23. Risks

Retailer hostility

Some retailers will not want an abstraction layer owning customer intent. The Amazon/Perplexity dispute is a clear warning.  

Thin access surfaces

Public API support is uneven, and some integrations will require partnerships rather than pure self-serve development.  

Wrong purchase risk

A single bad autonomous decision can damage trust disproportionately.

Margin compression

If the business relies only on affiliate economics, it may become operationally expensive without enough upside.

Support burden

Owning the transaction flow creates user expectations around reversal, support, and blame.

